POLICE in Mpumalanga are investigating three counts of murder after three people were found burnt beyond recognition in a car found outside Pienaar on Friday, 15 July. The discovery was made by a farm worker who then alerted the cops. Police spokesman Colonel Donald Mdluli said the car and the human remains were discovered by a farm worker who was going to the farm in the morning. He said on arrival at the scene, police found that there were human remains on the driver’s seat, passenger seat and also in the boot of the Hyundai i10. “The identity of the three is unknown at this stage. The circumstances surrounding this incident is being investigated by the police,” he said Police boss Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela has since strongly condemned the incident and called for the swift arrest of the suspects. “This is a horrible incident and a team of experts has been assembled to investigate this case and trace the perpetrators of this heinous crime. The perpetrators should be hunted down and be brought to book,” said Manamela. The police urge anyone with information that may assist in the investigation to call CrimeStop on 08600 10111, or send information via MYSAPSAPP. All information will be treated as confidential and callers may opt to remain anonymous.